                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1613a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Everett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-20T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 20, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Please telegraph any information which you can discreetly obtain in regard to
                    the reactions of the Permanent Mandates Commission to proposed British policy in
                    Palestine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
